<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,509,965]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,761,785]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nobili, G." box="[328,500,761,785]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="13 - 159" refId="ref51383" refString="Nobili, G. (1906 a) Crustaces decapodes et stomatopodes. In: Mission J. Bonnier et Ch. Perez (Golfe Persique, 1901). Bulletin Scientifique de la France et de la Belgique, 40, 13 - 159, pls. 2 - 7." type="journal article" year="1906">Nobili (1906a)</bibRefCitation>
originally described 
<emphasis box="[757,1211,762,785]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName authority="Jousseaumei" authorityName="Jousseaumei" box="[757,1034,762,785]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Paguristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Paguristes Jousseaumei</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[1048,1211,762,785]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" rank="variety" variety="perspicax">var. perspicax</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1293,1381,761,785]" name="Bahrain" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Bahrain</collectingCountry>
and Arzanah I. (Abu Dhabi) in the eastern Persian Gulf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rahayu, D. L." box="[756,925,797,821]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 42" refId="ref51666" refString="Rahayu, D. L. (2005) Additions to the Indonesian fauna of the hermit crab genus Pseudopaguristes McLaughlin and a further division of the genus Paguristes Dana (Crustacea: Decapoda: Paguroidea: Diogenidae). Zootaxa, 831, 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="2005">Rahayu (2005)</bibRefCitation>
assigned the species of this group including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nobili" authorityYear="1906" box="[151,388,834,857]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Paguristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perspicax">
<emphasis box="[151,388,834,857]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Paguristes perspicax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that are characterized by the possession of 12 pairs of gills to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson 1899" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1899" class="Liliopsida" family="Hydrocharitaceae" genus="Stratiotes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1216,1322,833,857]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Stratiotes</emphasis>
Thomson 1899
</taxonomicName>
, while the members of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Dana, 1851" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1851" box="[581,838,869,893]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Paguristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[581,701,870,893]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Paguristes</emphasis>
Dana, 1851
</taxonomicName>
, have 13 pairs of gills. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rahayu, D. L. &amp; McLaughlin, P. A." box="[1096,1436,869,893]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="67 - 68" refId="ref51772" refString="Rahayu, D. L. &amp; McLaughlin, P. A. (2010) Areopaguristes, a generic replacement name for Stratiotes Thomson, 1899 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Paguroidea: Diogenidae). Zootaxa, 2509, 67 - 68." type="journal article" year="2010">Rahayu &amp; McLaughlin (2010)</bibRefCitation>
realized that 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson 1899" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1899" box="[301,589,905,929]" class="Liliopsida" family="Hydrocharitaceae" genus="Stratiotes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[301,407,905,929]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Stratiotes</emphasis>
Thomson 1899
</taxonomicName>
was a junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Putzeys, 1846" authorityName="Putzeys" authorityYear="1846" box="[908,1187,905,930]" class="Liliopsida" family="Hydrocharitaceae" genus="Stratiotes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[908,1014,905,929]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Stratiotes</emphasis>
Putzeys, 1846
</taxonomicName>
, a coleopteran genus. Therefore, they subsequently proposed 
<taxonomicName authority="Rahayu &amp; McLaughlin, 2010" authorityName="Rahayu &amp; McLaughlin" authorityYear="2010" box="[593,1100,941,965]" class="Malacostraca" family="Diogenidae" genus="Areopaguristes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[593,763,941,965]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Areopaguristes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Rahayu, D. L. &amp; McLaughlin, P. A." box="[770,1100,941,965]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="67 - 68" refId="ref51772" refString="Rahayu, D. L. &amp; McLaughlin, P. A. (2010) Areopaguristes, a generic replacement name for Stratiotes Thomson, 1899 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Paguroidea: Diogenidae). Zootaxa, 2509, 67 - 68." type="journal article" year="2010">Rahayu &amp; McLaughlin, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a replacement name.
</paragraph>
